{"id": 231230790, "title": "F1 News: Alpine Readying Jack Doohan for Ocon Seat", "text": "The Alpine F1 Team is preparing for the 2025 racing season by considering reserve driver Jack Doohan as a potential successor to Esteban Ocon. With Ocon's contract set to conclude after the current season, Alpine is under pressure to fill the now-open seat. Alpine's team chief, Bruno Famin, recently highlighted Doohan's readiness during a Sky Sports F1 broadcast.Doohan's ascent within Alpine has been marked by a comprehensive testing schedule, underscoring the team's commitment to preparing him for a more substantial role. Famin commented on the breadth of Doohan's preparation, as quoted by F1i.\"I think he's an option, for sure. Jack is an option. We are preparing him.\"He was testing in Zandvoort some time ago and he has quite a heavy testing program. We are happy with that and let's see how he develops.\"Of course, nothing is confirmed. There are several other drivers in contention for the seat, including former Haas driver Mick Schumacher.\"He's one possibility among others, but he's one possibility, for sure,\" Famin concluded.Adding to his credentials, Doohan's participation in the mandatory rookie practice sessions has been a cornerstone of his evaluation. His involvement in the challenging and wet FP1 session at the Canadian Grand Prix provided a real-time test of his adaptability and skill. Despite limited running due to the heavy storm Montreal was experiencing, the Australian managed to gather valuable data.Describing the experience, Doohan said:\"It was not the most exciting FP1 session for me, with limited running due to the weather conditions... We were able to get an installation lap in with the wet tire and make sure the car was running fine.\"Meanwhile, Ocon remains in the seat for the rest of the season after confirming he and the team came to a mutual agreement for him to leave after a 5-year long tenure.\"We've been talking with the team for several months. It's the kind of team that is not taking decisions on just a single race,\" he told ESPN.\"We've agreed mutually to come to an end, basically at the end of the contract. I've spent five years inside this team five years in terms of Formula One world is a long time. Finish the collaboration on the high.\"As Alpine navigates these pivotal changes, the potential promotion of Doohan offers a glimpse into the 2025 season for the French squad. But with immense challenges felt so far this year, it will be nothing but an uphill battle.", "summary": "Alpine F1 is considering reserve driver Jack Doohan as a potential successor to Esteban Ocon for the 2025 season.", "url": "https://www.newsweek.com/sports/formula1/f1-news-alpine-readying-jack-doohan-ocon-seat-1910009", "image": "https://d.newsweek.com/en/full/2406293/esteban-ocon-alpine-f1-team.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 13:00:01", "author": "Alex Harrington", "authors": ["Alex Harrington"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "us", "sentiment": 0.109}